11#include "video/adaptation/encode_usage_resource.h"
12
13#include <limits>
14#include <utility>
15
16#include "rtc_base/checks.h"
17#include "rtc_base/ref_counted_object.h"
18
19namespace webrtc {
20
21// static
22rtc::scoped_refptr<EncodeUsageResource> EncodeUsageResource::Create(
23 std::unique_ptr<OveruseFrameDetector> overuse_detector) {
24 return rtc::make_ref_counted<EncodeUsageResource>(
25 std::move(overuse_detector));
26}
27
28EncodeUsageResource::EncodeUsageResource(
29 std::unique_ptr<OveruseFrameDetector> overuse_detector)
30 : VideoStreamEncoderResource("EncoderUsageResource"),
31 overuse_detector_(std::move(overuse_detector)),
32 is_started_(false),
33 target_frame_rate_(absl::nullopt) {
34 RTC_DCHECK(overuse_detector_);
35}
36
37EncodeUsageResource::~EncodeUsageResource() {}
38
39bool EncodeUsageResource::is_started() const {
40 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue());
41 return is_started_;
42}
43
44void EncodeUsageResource::StartCheckForOveruse(CpuOveruseOptions options) {
45 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue());
46 RTC_DCHECK(!is_started_);
47 overuse_detector_->StartCheckForOveruse(TaskQueueBase::Current(),
48 std::move(options), this);
49 is_started_ = true;
50 overuse_detector_->OnTargetFramerateUpdated(TargetFrameRateAsInt());
51}
52
53void EncodeUsageResource::StopCheckForOveruse() {
54 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue());
55 overuse_detector_->StopCheckForOveruse();
56 is_started_ = false;
57}
58
59void EncodeUsageResource::SetTargetFrameRate(
60 absl::optional<double> target_frame_rate) {
61 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue());
62 if (target_frame_rate == target_frame_rate_)
63 return;
64 target_frame_rate_ = target_frame_rate;
65 if (is_started_)
66 overuse_detector_->OnTargetFramerateUpdated(TargetFrameRateAsInt());
67}
68
69void EncodeUsageResource::OnEncodeStarted(const VideoFrame& cropped_frame,
70 int64_t time_when_first_seen_us) {
71 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue());
72 // TODO(hbos): Rename FrameCaptured() to something more appropriate (e.g.
73 // "OnEncodeStarted"?) or revise usage.
74 overuse_detector_->FrameCaptured(cropped_frame, time_when_first_seen_us);
75}
76
77void EncodeUsageResource::OnEncodeCompleted(
78 uint32_t timestamp,
79 int64_t time_sent_in_us,
80 int64_t capture_time_us,
81 absl::optional<int> encode_duration_us) {
82 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue());
83 // TODO(hbos): Rename FrameSent() to something more appropriate (e.g.
84 // "OnEncodeCompleted"?).
85 overuse_detector_->FrameSent(timestamp, time_sent_in_us, capture_time_us,
86 encode_duration_us);
87}
88
89void EncodeUsageResource::AdaptUp() {
90 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue());
91 OnResourceUsageStateMeasured(ResourceUsageState::kUnderuse);
92}
93
94void EncodeUsageResource::AdaptDown() {
95 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue());
96 OnResourceUsageStateMeasured(ResourceUsageState::kOveruse);
97}
98
99int EncodeUsageResource::TargetFrameRateAsInt() {
100 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(encoder_queue());
101 return target_frame_rate_.has_value()
102 ? static_cast<int>(target_frame_rate_.value())
103 : std::numeric_limits<int>::max();
104}
105
106} // namespace webrtc
